\end_layout

\begin_layout Definition
The set 
\begin_inset Formula $S$
\end_inset

 is called 
\series bold
\emph on
linearly dependent
\series default
\emph default
 (LD) if there is a 
\emph on
nonzero
\emph default
 vector 
\begin_inset Formula $\mathbf{x}\in\CC^{n}$
\end_inset

 such that 
\begin_inset Formula 
\[
\mathbf{a}_{1}x_{1}+\mathbf{a}_{2}x_{2}+\cdots+\mathbf{a}_{n}x_{n}=\mathbf{0}.
\]

\end_inset

If no such set of nonzero scalars exists, then we call 
\begin_inset Formula $S$
\end_inset

 
\series bold
\emph on
linearly independent
\series default
\emph default
 (LI).
 
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
\begin_inset Separator plain
\end_inset


\end_layout

