Solve 
\begin_inset Formula $A\mathbf{x}=\mathbf{0}$
\end_inset

 with
\begin_inset Formula 
\[
A=\left[\begin{array}{ccc}
1 & 2 & 3\\
0 & 0 & 0\\
0 & 0 & 0
\end{array}\right].
\]

\end_inset

No row reduction is needed.
 Only the first row is informative; we have one equation 
\begin_inset Formula 
\[
x_{1}+2x_{2}+3x_{3}=0
\]

\end_inset

in three unknowns.
 We have two free variables; set 
\begin_inset Formula $x_{2}=s$
\end_inset

 and 
\begin_inset Formula $x_{3}=t$
\end_inset

.
 Then 
\begin_inset Formula $x_{1}=-2s-3t$
\end_inset

, so any solution can be written as
\begin_inset Formula 
\[
\mathbf{x}=\left[\begin{array}{c}
-2s-3t\\
s\\
t
\end{array}\right].
\]

\end_inset

It is useful to write this as the sum of two vectors, each multiplied by
