\begin_inset Formula 
\[
\mathbf{x}=s_{1}\mathbf{v}_{1}+s_{2}\mathbf{v}_{2}+\cdots+s_{k}\mathbf{v}_{k}.
\]

\end_inset

The 
\begin_inset Formula $\mathbf{v}_{j}$
\end_inset

's form a basis for 
\begin_inset Formula $\Null\left(A\right)$
\end_inset

.
 
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Notice that the homogeneous equation 
\begin_inset Formula $A\mathbf{x}=\mathbf{0}$
\end_inset

 has either exactly one solution – the trivial solution 
\begin_inset Formula $\mathbf{x}=\mathbf{0}$
\end_inset

