 reduction produces no zero rows, then the solution 
\begin_inset Formula $\mathbf{x}$
\end_inset

 is constructed by backsubstitution.
 If no zeros appear on the diagonal, we call the matrix 
\series bold
\emph on
nonsingular
\series default
\emph default
.
 Otherwise, the matrix is called 
\series bold
\emph on
singular
\series default
\emph default
.
 
\end_layout

