\begin_inset Formula $P$
\end_inset

 is identical to the area of the rectangle outlined in blue dashed lines.
 The rectangle has sides of length 
\begin_inset Formula $\left\Vert \mathbf{a}\right\Vert $
\end_inset

 and 
\begin_inset Formula $\left\Vert \mathbf{b}\right\Vert \sin\theta_{ba}$
\end_inset

, so the area of 
\begin_inset Formula $P$
\end_inset

 is
\begin_inset Formula 
\begin{equation}
\text{Area}\left(P\right)=\left\Vert \mathbf{a}\right\Vert \left\Vert \mathbf{b}\right\Vert \sin\theta_{ba}.\label{eq:ParallelogramArea}
\end{equation}

\end_inset

We compute 
\begin_inset Formula $\sin\theta_{ba}$
\end_inset

 with angle addition:
\begin_inset Formula 
\[
\sin\theta_{ba}=\sin\left(\theta_{b}-\theta_{a}\right)
\]

\end_inset


\begin_inset Formula 
\[
=\cos\theta_{a}\sin\theta_{b}-\cos\theta_{b}\sin\theta_{a}
\]

\end_inset

which we can express in terms of the Cartesian components of 
\begin_inset Formula $\mathbf{a}$
\end_inset

 and 
\begin_inset Formula $\mathbf{b}$
\end_inset

